WebService-Leanpub version v0.3.1

This module provides a Perl interface to the web API of the publisher Leanpub.

To use the Leanpub API and therefore to use this module you need an API key
from Leanpub. To get an API key you have to sign in to leanpub and follow the
instruction at https://leanpub.com/help/api.

Using this perl module you are able to

* create book previews
* publish books
* query the job status of a preview or a publishing command
* get the summary sales data and
* get data about individual purchases
* create, list and update coupons for your book

from your perl program.

There is a accompanying command line program that allows you to use the
capabilities of this module from the command line and may serve you as an
example for your own code.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install


DEPENDENCIES

None.

